<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.248132>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Akatopora leucocypha (Marcus, 1937): A, portion of colony showing a number of zooids with interspersed kenozooids and thick and pillared calcification of side and basal walls. B, more highly magnified view of several zooids; the central zooid had been damaged and a smaller replacement zooid has grown inside the skeleton of the earlier zooid. C, close-up of a zooid surrounded by triangular kenozooids and an avicularium. Scale bars: A, 0.3 mm; B, C, 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/248132/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

